{"word":"δεσπότης","slug":"δεσπότης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>δεσπότης, ου, ὁ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el>δεσπόζω</el> ‘be lord/master’] <b><i>master</i><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> as <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ opp.\">opp.</a> of <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:δοῦλος\">δοῦλος</a></el> in the ordinary sense <b><a href='B:610 6:1'>1 Ti 6:1f</a>; <a href='B:630 2:9'>Tit 2:9</a>; <a href='B:670 2:18'>1 Pt 2:18</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> one who is <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ esp.\">esp.</a> recognized for superiority and claim on a <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pers.\">pers.</a>: of God <b><a href='B:490 2:29'>Lk 2:29</a></b> and <b><a href='B:510 4:24'>Ac 4:24</a></b> (in these two passages as correlative of <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:δοῦλος\">δοῦλος</a></el>); <b><a href='B:730 6:10'>Rv 6:10</a>;</b> of Christ <b><a href='B:680 2:1'>2 Pt 2:1</a>; <a href='B:720 1:1'>Jd 4</a>.—</b>As <i>owner</i> <b><a href='B:620 2:21'>2 Ti 2:21</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:δεσμώτης\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:δεῦρο\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}